PUH-BrianMartell Detailed Experimental Procedure for the Lattice-Shift Test — Understandable Step-by-Step This is the refined, executable procedure for the simple Lattice-Shift experiment (high-RPM rotor + torsional pendulum) to detect excess torsional drag from substrate ξ stiffening — a direct test of PUH vs standard GR/elasticity. Goal: Measure periodic torque on pendulum exceeding GR prediction by ~10^{-12–10}. Materials (low-cost, mostly off-shelf): •  High-density tungsten rotor (~1 kg, balanced, diameter ~10 cm). •  Electric motor/vacuum chamber capable of 50,000–100,000 RPM sustained. •  Ultra-sensitive torsional pendulum (quartz fiber ~1 m, mirror mass ~10 g). •  Laser interferometer (HeNe, ~10^{-15} rad sensitivity). •  Vacuum ~10^{-6} Torr to eliminate air drag. •  Isolation table (seismic damping).
